20/* We don't have insn-modes.h, but we include tm.h. */
21#define BITS_PER_UNIT 8
22
23#include "bconfig.h"
24#include "system.h"
25#include "coretypes.h"
26#include "tm.h"
27
28#define DEFTREECODE(SYM, NAME, TYPE, LEN) #SYM,
29#define END_OF_BASE_TREE_CODES
30
31static const char *const tree_codes[] = {
32#include "all-tree.def"
33(char*) 0
34};
35
36#undef DEFTREECODE
37#undef END_OF_BASE_TREE_CODES
38
39static void usage (void);
40
41static void
42usage (void)
43{
44 fputs ("Usage: gencheck\n", stderr);
45}
46
47int
48main (int argc, char ** ARG_UNUSED (argv))
49{
50 int i, j;
51
52 switch (argc)
53 {
54 case 1:
55 break;
56
57 default:
58 usage ();
59 return (1);
60 }
61
62 puts ("/* This file is generated using gencheck. Do not edit. */\n");
63 puts ("#ifndef GCC_TREE_CHECK_H");
64 puts ("#define GCC_TREE_CHECK_H\n");
65
66 /* Print macros for checks based on each of the tree code names. However,
67 since we include the tree nodes from all languages, we must check
68 for duplicate names to avoid defining the same macro twice. */
69 for (i = 0; tree_codes[i]; i++)
70 {
71 for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
72 if (strcmp (tree_codes[i], tree_codes[j]) == 0)
73 break;
74
75 if (i == j)
76 printf ("#define %s_CHECK(t)\tTREE_CHECK (t, %s)\n",
77 tree_codes[i], tree_codes[i]);
78 }
79
80 puts ("\n#endif /* GCC_TREE_CHECK_H */");
81 return 0;
82}
